race.comment: EVERY LITTLE THING (7) resumed with a near miss at Mornington over 1200m and has had excuses her two outings since especially the latest at Yarra Valley. Peaks for this and John Allen rides today. SLATE RIPPER (5) comes out pof the same race beaten just 1.5L. He drew wide and settled last, and there was plenty of merit in the effort. Maps for a soft run today and should go close. MARIOTA (3) settled rearward and made up a little ground over 1400m at Sale. He comes back a couple of steps in grade and can settle close from an inside gate. His best form would have him in the finish. EAU DE COLOGNE (1) is sure to show more third up. Has pieces of form that would see him competitive. SPIRIT ANGEL (10) brings a 3L win from Hanging Rock over 1800m at 52 level. Needs a good ride but should be around the mark.
